I"É<p>After discovering that someone has started and <a href="https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=211400">Arch Forum thread for this machine</a>, I was prompted with this issue.  I use keyboard shortcuts to suspend and lock this laptop alreay.  I usually just hit the hotkey(s), close the lid, and never think twice about it (the solution Iâ€™m suggesting here).</p>

<p>However, if you were to close the lid (triggering suspend) and open it (triggering resume), youâ€™ll find that the machine will randomly suspend itself again.  You can click to resume, but eventually the system will freeze; requiring a hard reboot.</p>

<p>A possible workaround is to disable systemdâ€™s control over the lid and manually use a keyboard shortcut to run a given suspend / lock command prior to closing the lid.</p>

<p>1) Disable <em>systemd</em>â€™s control over actions-on-lid-close:</p>

